A: You can use explicit wait to wait until the Facebook login popup is visible and then interact with the elements inside it.
Here is an example:
WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 10);
WebElement fbLoginPopup = wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.cssSelector("div[aria-label='Facebook Login']")));

// Now you can interact with the elements inside the popup
WebElement emailField = fbLoginPopup.findElement(By.id("email"));
emailField.sendKeys("selenium");

This code will wait up to 10 seconds for the Facebook login popup to be visible. If the popup is not visible after 10 seconds, it will throw a NoSuchElementException.

